  "prompt": "How can we define UPSC?",
  "response": "UPSC stands for the **Union Public Service Commission**, which is India's central recruiting agency. It is responsible for conducting various examinations for appointment to the civil services of the Government of India. The most prominent exam conducted by UPSC is the **Civil Services Examination (CSE)**, which selects candidates for various prestigious positions within the Indian Administrative Service (IAS), Indian Police Service (IPS), Indian Foreign Service (IFS), and other central services.\n\nThe UPSC is established under Article 315 of the Constitution of India and operates independently of the government to ensure a fair and impartial selection process. The commission also conducts other examinations, including those for engineering services, medical services, and other specialized professions, ensuring that candidates are selected based on merit.",
